## 🧰 Tier 5: The Forensic Triage & Data Recovery Lab (SystemRescue)

SystemRescue is a Linux system rescue disk available as a bootable ISO image. Deploying it as a permanent utility VM inside Proxmox allows you to hot-plug degraded virtual disks or raw network storage blocks straight into a dedicated recovery environment.

### 🛠️ Step A: Provisioning the Rescue Appliance

1. Download the latest **SystemRescue ISO** image directly into your Proxmox ISO storage template pool.
2. Create a new VM on your Dell R710 host:
* **CPU/RAM:** 2 vCPUs, 2–4 GB RAM.
* **OS:** Select the SystemRescue ISO as the boot media.
* **Network:** Attach to your isolated lab bridge (`vmbr1`).


3. Set the VM boot options to boot from the CD-ROM drive first. When launched, it will boot directly into a live, non-destructive Linux command-line environment loaded with every open-source forensic tool available.

